            <div class="b-comment">
	<a href="#" class="scroll-wrapper" name="15364"></a>
	<div class="comment" id="comment_15364">
			<div class="b-post-author g-approved-user">
					<div class="l-avatar">
						<a class="avatar" href="https://dou.ua/users/uranium/">
							<div class="g-avatar">	<img src="https://s.dou.ua/img/avatars/40x40_3451.jpg" user="3451" title="Serhiy Brytskyy" width="40" height="40" alt="Serhiy Brytskyy" srcset="https://s.dou.ua/img/avatars/80x80_3451.jpg 1.1x">
</div>
							Serhiy Brytskyy
						</a>
					</div>

				<span class="prof">
						<a class="company" href="https://jobs.dou.ua/companies/globallogic/" target="_blank"><span class="company-favicon" style="background: url(https://s.dou.ua/img/static/favicons/gl.png) no-repeat;">GlobalLogic</span></a>
				</span>


				<a class="comment-link" href="#15364">24 октября 2007 9:05</a>
			</div>

		<div class="l-text b-typo">
			<div><p>I&nbsp;would like to&nbsp;take this opportunity to&nbsp;announce the beginning of&nbsp;a&nbsp;new period of&nbsp;exciting times for SoftServe.</p>

<p>As&nbsp;everyone knows, SoftServe has been growing at&nbsp;a&nbsp;very rapid pace. However, all of&nbsp;us also feel the strain on&nbsp;the organization as&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;such rapid growth. For some time we&nbsp;have been seeking a&nbsp;solution that will allow&nbsp;us to&nbsp;continue our growth, but with better control and direction. We&nbsp;considered many options including speaking with potential acquirers, with the idea that a&nbsp;strategic acquirer with experience in&nbsp;running larger operations could help&nbsp;us organize ourselves to&nbsp;achieve higher growth rates more smoothly.</p>

<p>In&nbsp;the end, we&nbsp;decided that remaining an&nbsp;independent fast growth company, but with a&nbsp;change in&nbsp;organizational structure, leadership and leadership structure was the best for&nbsp;us and best for all of&nbsp;you. It&nbsp;will provide for more opportunities for career growth. It&nbsp;will provide for more stability in&nbsp;staff positions. It&nbsp;will assure that we&nbsp;can control our own destiny, something we&nbsp;have become even more excited about as&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;these upcoming changes.</p>

<p>What are the changes?</p>

<p>We&nbsp;are creating a&nbsp;new legal entity that will own only our Offshore Software Development business. The main reason for this is&nbsp;to&nbsp;reduce the distractions and improve the focus on&nbsp;our core business. It&nbsp;will also allow&nbsp;us to&nbsp;more effectively plan for and use our financial resources to&nbsp;grow the OSD&nbsp;business.</p>

<p>We&nbsp;are changing our leadership structure to&nbsp;have a&nbsp;three tier decision hierarchy. The shareholders of&nbsp;SoftServe will elect a&nbsp;Board of&nbsp;Directors based on&nbsp;experience and ability to&nbsp;guide&nbsp;us through our future growth and evolution. The Board of&nbsp;Directors will choose the management of&nbsp;the company and provide strategic direction and guidance in&nbsp;building the business.</p>

<p>Some of&nbsp;you may remember Vil Ezerins. Vil owned two companies that were former SoftServe clients (Alvion and AccuData). We&nbsp;have developed a&nbsp;close friendship with Vil since that time and we&nbsp;have often consulted with him on&nbsp;some of&nbsp;the difficult management questions we&nbsp;have encountered. Some of&nbsp;you met him recently when he&nbsp;was here. The main purpose of&nbsp;his visit was to&nbsp;meet some of&nbsp;our people and to&nbsp;learn about the various issues we&nbsp;face every day, to&nbsp;evaluate the potential to&nbsp;become more deeply involved with SoftServe.</p>

<p>We&nbsp;are happy to&nbsp;report that he&nbsp;has chosen to&nbsp;invest in&nbsp;SoftServe and to&nbsp;join our Board of&nbsp;Directors as&nbsp;Chairman. He&nbsp;possesses unique qualifications for a&nbsp;company such as&nbsp;us...he is&nbsp;a&nbsp;former SoftServe client, he&nbsp;built and sold his own&nbsp;IT company with significant operations in&nbsp;Ukraine (Sevastopol) and he&nbsp;has very close ties to&nbsp;Ukraine through his investments in&nbsp;real estate in&nbsp;Ukraine. Vil’s role will be&nbsp;to&nbsp;lead, develop and guide our management team to&nbsp;prepare for our future success as&nbsp;a&nbsp;much larger enterprise. As&nbsp;we&nbsp;had previously announced, we&nbsp;also want to&nbsp;establish a&nbsp;USA headquarters for SoftServe. Vil resides in&nbsp;the USA and will be&nbsp;responsible for setting that up&nbsp;for&nbsp;us. We&nbsp;believe this will allow&nbsp;us to&nbsp;acquire, service and satisfy significantly larger clients than we&nbsp;are now able to&nbsp;attract.</p>

<p>Please welcome Vil (<a href="mailto:vezerins@softservecom.com">vezerins@softservecom.com</a>) to&nbsp;SoftServe.</p>

<p>We&nbsp;are accepting outside financial investment for the first time in&nbsp;our history. We&nbsp;have decided and realized that in&nbsp;order to&nbsp;compete on&nbsp;a&nbsp;large scale with global OSD&nbsp;competition, we&nbsp;need to&nbsp;implement a&nbsp;full set of&nbsp;industry best practices, which includes significant investment in&nbsp;third party tools that will organize our work so&nbsp;it&nbsp;is&nbsp;easier to&nbsp;manage a&nbsp;larger scale enterprise and deliver better quality results as&nbsp;we&nbsp;scale. As&nbsp;a&nbsp;result of&nbsp;this investment, we&nbsp;will now have a&nbsp;significant budget to&nbsp;purchase and implement the very best tools on&nbsp;the market that support the successful delivery of&nbsp;our services to&nbsp;customers, ranging from testing tools to&nbsp;requirements management to&nbsp;estimating tools, as&nbsp;well as&nbsp;improved “back end” support tools, such as&nbsp;performance management, resource planning, etc. It&nbsp;will also allow&nbsp;us to&nbsp;enter new markets where customers demand an&nbsp;expensive infrastructure of&nbsp;tool sets to&nbsp;manage and deliver their services to&nbsp;them. </p>

<p>We&nbsp;are confident that such investments will exponentially increase the advantage we&nbsp;have against our Central &amp;&nbsp;Eastern European competitors, and it&nbsp;will put is&nbsp;perfectly in&nbsp;alignment with the very best competitors we&nbsp;have on&nbsp;a&nbsp;global level. </p>

<p>Sincerely,</p>

<p>Taras Kytsmey<br>President, Softserve, Inc.</p></div>
		</div>

